Phone
The Phone refers to the new device that users are setting up, including accessories and pre-installed features.

Power Adapter
The Power Adapter is a necessary accessory for charging the phone, included with most new devices.

SIM Ejector Tool
A SIM Ejector Tool is used to open the SIM card tray in phones, provided typically within the packaging.

User Manual/Warranty Card
These documents provide guidance on device usage and warranty information, included with most new phones.

Screen Protector
A Screen Protector is applied to the phoneâ€™s screen for durability and scratch resistance; some are pre-installed.

MicroSD Card
A MicroSD Card expands the storage capacity of a smartphone, if supported by the device.

eSIM Technology
eSIM technology allows for wireless mobile network activation and SIM card management on compatible phones.

Wi-Fi Network
A Wi-Fi Network enables internet connectivity for smartphones without using cellular data.

Google Account
Google Account is essential for accessing Google services, including cloud backup and app store access on Android devices.

Apple ID
An Apple ID allows users to access iCloud services and the App Store on iOS devices.

Find My Device
A security feature available for Android devices, enabling tracking of lost phones through a Google Account.<SEP>Find My Device is a security feature that helps locate a lost or stolen phone, which should be enabled to enhance device security.

Google Drive/ iCloud
Cloud storage services provided by Google and Apple respectively, used for backing up data on mobile devices.

Google Play Store/App Store
App stores provided by Google for Android and Apple for iOS devices, where users can download applications.

Bloatware
Pre-installed apps on new smartphones that may not be useful to the user; they can often be disabled or uninstalled.

SIM card
The SIM card is used in the process of activating mobile services on the phone, essential for making calls, sending texts, and accessing mobile data.

Mobile Data
Mobile Data refers to internet connectivity provided by a cellular network, necessary for browsing and using online apps when Wi-Fi is unavailable.

Wi-Fi Connection
Wi-Fi Connection allows devices to connect to the internet wirelessly within range of a router, important for data usage without consuming mobile data.

Front Camera
The Front Camera on the phone is used primarily for selfies and video calls, requiring functionality checks during setup.

Rear Camera
The Rear Camera is typically the primary camera on a smartphone, used for general photography; its performance needs to be verified in the setup process.

Speakers
The Speakers are components that output audio from the phone, tested by playing videos or music during setup to ensure they work properly.

Microphone
The Microphone captures sound for calls and voice commands; it is tested by recording audio or making a call to verify its functionality.

Biometric Security
Biometric Security features, such as fingerprint scanning or facial recognition, provide secure phone unlocking methods and require testing for accuracy during setup.

Automatic Backups
Automatic Backups are settings configured to regularly save data on cloud services, preventing loss of information and facilitating easy recovery.

Brightness Settings
Brightness settings allow users to adjust screen brightness according to their preferences for optimal viewing.

Dark Mode
Dark mode is a display setting that uses dark colors as the primary background, reducing eye strain in low-light conditions.

Notification Sounds
Notification sounds are customizable audio alerts that notify users of various events or messages on their device.

Widgets
Widgets are small applications that display specific information like a clock, weather updates, etc., directly on the home screen for quick access.

Home Screen
The home screen is the main interface of a smartphone where apps and widgets can be organized and accessed easily.

Frequently Used Apps
These are applications that users frequently interact with, which can be grouped into folders for easier access on the home screen.
